mmaapp_ppvv() -- Memory-Manipulation Routine

vvaaddddrr_tt
mmaapp_ppvv(_p_a_d_d_r, _l_e_n)
ppaaddddrr_tt _p_a_d_d_r;
ffssiizzee_tt _l_e_n;

mmaapp_ppvv()  initializes  a  virtual  address  to  access physical  memory  at
location _p_a_d_d_r  of size  _l_e_n bytes.   It provides read  and write  (but not
execute)  access.  When  no longer  required, a  virtual address  should be
released by invoking uunnmmaapp_ppvv().

